@page
@using WebSpark.Bootswatch.Demo.Pages
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="container py-3">
    <h2>Your Privacy Matters</h2>
    <p class="lead">Last Updated: May 4, 2025</p>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h3 class="mb-0">Overview</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>This privacy policy explains how WebSpark.Bootswatch.Demo ("we," "our," or "us") collects and processes
                information when you visit our website. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring
                transparency in our data practices.</p>
            <p>This is a read-only demonstration site. We <strong>do not</strong> collect or store personally
                identifiable information about visitors.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h3 class="mb-0">Information We Collect</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4>Anonymous Usage Data</h4>
            <p>We collect anonymous usage data to improve our website and understand visitor patterns. This information
                includes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Browser type and version</li>
                <li>Operating system</li>
                <li>Referring website</li>
                <li>Time and date of visit</li>
                <li>Pages visited</li>
                <li>General geographic location (city/country level only)</li>
                <li>Device type (desktop, tablet, mobile)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>This information is collected in an anonymous, aggregated form and cannot be used to identify individual
                users.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h3 class="mb-0">Analytics Tools We Use</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>We use industry-standard analytics tools to help us understand website usage patterns and improve user
                experience:</p>

            <h4>Azure Application Insights</h4>
            <p>We use Azure Application Insights to monitor website performance, track usage patterns, and identify
                potential issues. This service collects anonymous telemetry data to help us improve site performance and
                user experience. No personally identifiable information is collected.</p>

            <h4>Google Analytics</h4>
            <p>We may use Google Analytics to understand visitor behavior in aggregate. We have configured our
                implementation to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Anonymize IP addresses</li>
                <li>Disable data sharing with Google</li>
                <li>Disable User-ID tracking</li>
                <li>Respect "Do Not Track" browser settings</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Microsoft Clarity</h4>
            <p>We may use Microsoft Clarity to analyze anonymous user interactions through heatmaps and session
                recordings. All personal information such as IP addresses, email addresses, or phone numbers that may
                appear on screen are automatically masked. No keystroke data is recorded, and session recordings only
                capture mouse movements, clicks, and scrolling behavior.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h3 class="mb-0">Cookies</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>We use essential cookies for the basic functionality of our site, including remembering your theme
                preference. We also use analytics cookies that help us understand how visitors interact with our
                website.</p>
            <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling cookies may affect your experience on
                our website.</p>
            <h4>Cookie Types:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Functional cookies:</strong> These cookies (like "bootswatch-theme") remember your
                    preferences to enhance your experience.</li>
                <li><strong>Analytics cookies:</strong> These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our
                    website by collecting anonymous information.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h3 class="mb-0">Your Rights and Choices</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Opt out of analytics tracking by enabling "Do Not Track" in your browser settings</li>
                <li>Disable cookies through your browser settings</li>
                <li>Use private browsing mode to avoid tracking</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h3 class="mb-0">Data Security</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>We implement appropriate security measures to protect any data we collect. The anonymous data we gather
                is stored securely on Microsoft Azure servers with industry-standard security controls.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h3 class="mb-0">Changes to This Policy</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. The latest version will always be posted on this
                page with the effective date.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h3 class="mb-0">Contact Information</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact us:</p>
            <address>
                <strong>WebSpark.Bootswatch Team</strong><br>
                <a href="https://github.com/markhazleton/WebSpark.Bootswatch/issues" target="_blank">GitHub Issues
                    Page</a>
            </address>
            <p>For any privacy concerns or questions, please create an issue on our GitHub repository.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

           
           
           
           
           
           
           
           
           
           
           
           
           
        
           
               
               
           
           